    "what_description": "Elatostema tutuilense is a species of flowering plant in the family Urticaceae. It is a perennial herb with a woody base, growing up to 30 centimeters in height, and has cordate or ovate leaves that are 1-6 centimeters in length, with the upper surface being glabrous and the lower surface being pubescent. The leaves have 3-5 pairs of lateral veins and a cordate or rounded base. Elatostema tutuilense produces white or greenish flowers in axillary clusters, with the corolla being 0.5-1.5 millimeters in length and the stamens being 1-2 millimeters long. It is endemic to the island of Tutuila in American Samoa, where it grows in shaded, humid areas.",
