    "taxonomy": "Elatostema tutuilense is a species of flowering plant in the family Urticaceae, commonly known as the nettle family. This plant is native to the island of Tutuila in American Samoa. As a member of the Urticaceae family, Elatostema tutuilense is classified as a member of the order Urticales, which is a group of flowering plants that are often found in tropical and subtropical regions. The family Urticaceae is part of the larger clade of flowering plants known as angiosperms. The plant's classification is also reflected in its botanical name, Elatostema tutuilense, which is a combination of its genus and species designations.",
